# Highway Maintenance Management System Requirements

## Functional Requirements
1.System should provide secure login with role-based access (admin, maintenance staff, manager).
2.System should allow maintenance record management (create, update, archive records for highways, bridges, tunnels).
3.System should automate inspection scheduling based on triggered events (accidents, weather damage).
4.System able to generate work orders from inspection findings with tasks, deadlines, and assigned staff.
5.System must maintain asset database for highways (road sections, bridges, signage, lighting) with condition status.
6.System should enable incident reporting with photos and geolocation (potholes, cracks, accidents).
7.System should track workflow from inspection initiation to completion, including approvals and follow-ups.
8.System should send notifications and alerts for upcoming inspections, overdue tasks, or urgent maintenance.
9.System should support document and media storage (inspection reports, photos, videos, manuals).
10.System should provide analytics and reporting on inspection frequency, maintenance costs, asset condition trends, compliance.
11.System should integrate with GIS/maps to visualize highway sections and inspection points.
12.System should maintain audit trail and compliance tracking for accountability and government regulations.

## Non-Functional Requirements
1.System should ensure performance efficiency by handling at least 500 concurrent users without degradation.
2.System should guarantee security through encrypted data transmission and secure authentication protocols.
3.System should provide usability with intuitive navigation and accessible design for all staff roles.
4.System should maintain reliability by achieving 99% uptime and automatic recovery from failures.
5.System should support scalability to accommodate future expansion of assets, users, and inspection records.
6.System should ensure maintainability with modular architecture and clear documentation for updates and debugging.
